==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Promerit
<hw>Pro*mer"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>promeritus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>promerere</ets> to deserve;
<ets>pro</ets> before + <ets>merere</ets> to merit.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To oblige; to confer a favor on.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deserve; to procure by merit.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Davenant.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Promerops</ent>⟦br⟧
